# Trivy ignore file
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
#
# Suppress known false positives. Each entry MUST include:
#   - The CVE or finding ID
#   - An expiry date (exp:YYYY-MM-DD) so it gets reviewed
#   - A justification comment on the preceding line
#
# Example:
# # Not affected: we never call the vulnerable code path. Review by 2026-12-01.
# CVE-2021-12345 exp:2026-12-01
